WEBVTT

00:01.880 --> 00:03.460
Dre: New life. A miracle.

00:03.460 --> 00:04.880
One cell becomes two,

00:04.880 --> 00:08.330
then four, then -- boom --
a baby.

00:08.330 --> 00:10.790
As proud as we are as dads,

00:10.790 --> 00:13.830
it can't compare to the way
a mama feels about her baby.

00:13.830 --> 00:17.080
Being a new mom is the happiest
time in a woman's life.

00:17.080 --> 00:20.040
Mother Nature has given women
everything they need

00:20.040 --> 00:22.500
to sustain life
with comfort and ease.

00:22.500 --> 00:24.620
And Bow was no exception.

00:24.620 --> 00:27.500
Her time with her new babies
was always magic.

00:27.500 --> 00:29.830
Until now.

00:29.830 --> 00:31.580
Oh.

00:31.580 --> 00:33.580
♪♪

00:40.920 --> 00:42.830
Dre: Say "Jumpman."

00:42.830 --> 00:43.880
Say "Jordan."

00:43.880 --> 00:45.040
Come on, DeVonté.

00:45.040 --> 00:46.290
Say "Jordan."

00:46.290 --> 00:48.290
Hey, babe, look.
His first Jordans.

00:48.290 --> 00:49.500
[ All talking baby talk ]

00:49.500 --> 00:50.500
Huh?

00:50.500 --> 00:52.500
Cute.

00:52.500 --> 00:54.710
Yep, something was off
with Bow,

00:54.710 --> 00:56.830
and it was starting
to make me nervous.

00:56.830 --> 00:59.540
It was starting to make us
all nervous.

00:59.540 --> 01:02.290
So we all know that Dad
is an unreliable parent.

01:02.290 --> 01:03.330
Inept.
Useless.

01:03.330 --> 01:04.290
Embarrassing.

01:04.290 --> 01:05.830
And we've all noticed

01:05.830 --> 01:07.460
that Mom's been
a little off lately.

01:07.460 --> 01:08.460
A little?

01:08.460 --> 01:12.250
♪♪

01:12.250 --> 01:13.670
I've noticed it, too.

01:13.670 --> 01:16.210
Zoey! Freeze!

01:16.210 --> 01:17.540
Where you going?

01:17.540 --> 01:18.880
A party.

01:18.880 --> 01:20.040
Here's a fun idea.

01:20.040 --> 01:21.500
Take your brother.

01:21.500 --> 01:23.670
Yep.

01:23.670 --> 01:24.830
Oh.

01:24.830 --> 01:26.620
Perfect.

01:26.620 --> 01:28.000
Have fun.

01:28.000 --> 01:30.210
I don't know, guys.
She seems fine to me.

01:30.210 --> 01:32.170
♪♪

01:32.170 --> 01:35.540
[ Sobbing ]

01:35.540 --> 01:37.210
That's why it's so important

01:37.210 --> 01:39.290
we help Mom get back
on her feet.

01:39.290 --> 01:41.880
We can't let Dad be DeVonté's
sole provider.

01:41.880 --> 01:42.710
God no.
Nightmare.

01:42.710 --> 01:43.710
Doomed.

01:43.710 --> 01:45.790
Se we all need to help out.

01:45.790 --> 01:47.330
Make this house warm,

01:47.330 --> 01:48.750
nurturing, and safe.

01:48.750 --> 01:50.500
Right now, it's a death trap.

01:50.500 --> 01:52.710
I don't know, guys.
It seems fine to me.

01:52.710 --> 01:55.000
♪♪

01:56.290 --> 01:58.620
I can do "thank you" notes
for the dumb baby gifts we got.

01:58.620 --> 02:00.000
Perfect. Zoey?

02:00.000 --> 02:01.670
I'm thinking my role is gonna be

02:01.670 --> 02:03.000
more like his cool aunt.

02:03.000 --> 02:05.040
How about I skip this
and let him sleep on my futon

02:05.040 --> 02:06.250
after he gets
a girl pregnant?

02:06.250 --> 02:08.500
Um...okay.

02:08.500 --> 02:10.000
I guess this means I need

02:10.000 --> 02:11.790
to nurture this baby myself...

02:12.750 --> 02:14.290
[ Gasps ]
Oh, my God.

02:14.290 --> 02:15.710
...by giving him as much

02:15.710 --> 02:18.040
skin-to-skin contact
as possible.

02:18.040 --> 02:20.380
♪♪

02:20.380 --> 02:22.830
He's not right.

02:22.830 --> 02:24.960
I don't know, guys.
He seems fine to me.

02:24.960 --> 02:28.120
Bow was so down,
I resorted to an old move --

02:28.120 --> 02:29.880
straight-up lying.

02:29.880 --> 02:33.120
There's my radiant queen!

02:33.120 --> 02:34.460
How are you, beautiful?

02:34.460 --> 02:36.380
Fine.
I went to the store today.

02:36.380 --> 02:40.170
[ Sobbing ] But I don't need
this many potatoes!

02:40.170 --> 02:41.670
[ Sobbing ]

02:41.670 --> 02:43.790
That's great, you know.
They -- 'Cause you've, uh...

02:43.790 --> 02:45.120
You've always been
a good shopper.

02:45.120 --> 02:46.710
What's that you now
you say?

02:46.710 --> 02:48.000
77 degrees?

02:48.000 --> 02:49.710
77 degrees.
That seems warm.

02:49.710 --> 02:51.420
Is that too warm?
Is 77 too warm?

02:51.420 --> 02:53.210
Babe, if it is, just --

02:53.210 --> 02:54.620
just turn it down
if you're worried about it.

02:54.620 --> 02:56.750
Well, I can't turn it down, Dre.
I got to dry the tubes.

02:56.750 --> 02:58.380
I got to dry the tubes,
okay?
Okay, okay.

02:58.380 --> 02:59.790
You know what?
You want a massage?

02:59.790 --> 03:00.710
'Cause I can call Yvonne,

03:00.710 --> 03:02.120
and she can come by and give --

03:02.120 --> 03:03.670
Is he breathing?
I can't tell if he's breathing.

03:03.670 --> 03:05.250
Is he breathing?

03:05.250 --> 03:06.670
Um...
Let me go check.
I can't see.

03:06.670 --> 03:08.000
Okay. All right.
He doesn't look like
he's breathing.

03:08.000 --> 03:10.040
Uh, b-babe, you're --
you're glowing!

03:10.040 --> 03:12.330
You're glowing, babe!

03:12.330 --> 03:13.750
Mm.

03:13.750 --> 03:14.710
I'm worried about her.

03:14.710 --> 03:16.040
Yeah, you should be.

03:16.040 --> 03:17.460
Clearly,
she's cheating on you.

03:17.460 --> 03:19.750
No, this is what new motherhood
looks like.

03:19.750 --> 03:20.880
She's just weak.

03:20.880 --> 03:22.380
Look, I don't even
recognize her.

03:22.380 --> 03:24.080
She's not acting
like her normal self.

03:24.080 --> 03:25.580
And -- And I don't know
what to do.

03:25.580 --> 03:28.460
This never happened when
any of the other kids were born.

03:28.460 --> 03:31.580
Well, the twins were born
a long time ago.

03:31.580 --> 03:34.000
Earl was still on his original
Social Security number.

03:34.000 --> 03:36.210
Hmm. 1...

03:36.210 --> 03:38.920
6...4...

03:38.920 --> 03:40.210
Mm.
It's nice to know that

03:40.210 --> 03:41.750
I can always come talk
to you guys.

03:41.750 --> 03:42.620
-Uh-huh.
-We're always here for you.

03:42.620 --> 03:45.080
Yeah. Appreciate it.

03:45.080 --> 03:47.960
No, Jack, if something has
a skull and crossbones on it,

03:47.960 --> 03:48.920
it's not for pirates.

03:48.920 --> 03:50.790
It's poison.

03:50.790 --> 03:52.420
Ooh.
Sorry about that.

03:52.420 --> 03:54.960
The kids are trying to help out
by babyproofing the house.

03:54.960 --> 03:57.170
Back in my day,
"babyproofing" meant

03:57.170 --> 03:59.080
demanding proof
the baby was yours.

03:59.080 --> 04:00.620
[ Laughs ]

04:00.620 --> 04:02.580
Zingo!
Mm-hmm.

04:02.580 --> 04:04.580
Uh, but, seriously, though,
why are we so overprotective?

04:04.580 --> 04:06.540
You know, when do we stop
babying the kids

04:06.540 --> 04:08.250
and just let them fend
for themselves?

04:08.250 --> 04:09.830
Bup-bup-bup!
Did you clean your hands?

04:09.830 --> 04:11.380
Yes, Papa.
Mm?

04:11.380 --> 04:13.040
No, Papa.
No.

04:13.040 --> 04:14.880
Here you go.

04:14.880 --> 04:16.960
All over. In between.
There you go.

04:16.960 --> 04:18.420
Back of your neck.

04:18.420 --> 04:20.080
Good boy.

04:20.080 --> 04:21.120
Babyproofing.

04:21.120 --> 04:22.750
Remember
when we were young,

04:22.750 --> 04:25.210
and you'd ride around
in the trunk with your air hole,

04:25.210 --> 04:27.080
hoping that they remember
to let you out

04:27.080 --> 04:28.380
so you could see
the fireworks?

04:28.380 --> 04:31.250
Mm. Luckily for our kids,
we know better.

04:31.250 --> 04:33.330
Yeah, I never threw Eustace
in the trunk

04:33.330 --> 04:35.080
and drove to Tulsa for
Fourth of July weekend,

04:35.080 --> 04:37.790
so stop asking me
about it!

04:39.000 --> 04:41.750
Uh...Dre, why are you making
your kids babyproof the house?

04:41.750 --> 04:44.000
Oh, I'm not making them.
They want to help.

04:44.000 --> 04:46.290
Bow's been having a hard time
since the baby.

04:46.290 --> 04:48.710
You know, anxious,
not sleeping, crying a lot.

04:48.710 --> 04:51.040
This may help.

04:51.040 --> 04:52.920
It's my divorce attorney.

04:52.920 --> 04:55.670
She's super hot.
You know what I'm saying?

04:55.670 --> 04:57.460
Call her.
Oh, my God.

04:57.460 --> 05:00.040
Um, Dre, it just sounds like
Bow's got the baby blues.

05:00.040 --> 05:01.670
Mm.
What?

05:01.670 --> 05:03.460
Cat Stevens got it after
she had her litter.

05:03.460 --> 05:06.210
Been there.
My wife, she had it bad.

05:06.210 --> 05:08.830
For two years
after Eustace was born.

05:08.830 --> 05:10.750
Booked a trip to Acapulco
with my brother.

05:12.880 --> 05:14.500
Hard seeing her like that.

05:14.500 --> 05:16.000
Dre: Yeah, I just wish
there was a way

05:16.000 --> 05:17.750
I could find out
what's wrong with Bow.

05:17.750 --> 05:19.210
Y-You know,
I-I keep asking her,

05:19.210 --> 05:21.120
but she just keeps saying
she's fine.

05:21.120 --> 05:24.380
Well, as someone who hates
talking to women,

05:24.380 --> 05:27.120
I find that reading
ladies' magazines

05:27.120 --> 05:29.580
is a great insight
into where their heads are at.

05:29.580 --> 05:31.420
Really?
Josh: For sure.

05:31.420 --> 05:33.250
I took a Cosmo quiz once
to find out

05:33.250 --> 05:35.830
if I was a wallflower
or a night-blooming jasmine.

05:35.830 --> 05:38.960
Mm-hmm.
But I got kicked out of Curves
before I could finish it.

05:38.960 --> 05:42.620
♪♪

05:42.620 --> 05:43.670
Oh, I'm done babyproofing.

05:43.670 --> 05:46.790
Shh!

05:46.790 --> 05:48.330
[ Whispering ]
Let's have a look.

05:48.330 --> 05:50.670
♪♪

05:50.670 --> 05:53.000
You call this
babyproofing?

05:53.000 --> 05:55.170
Loose Legos?

05:55.170 --> 05:56.330
Do you want him
to choke?

05:57.620 --> 05:59.170
Or get strangled?

05:59.170 --> 06:03.210
♪♪

06:03.210 --> 06:05.920
Is this broken glass?!

06:05.920 --> 06:07.670
Is this a joke
to you people?!

06:07.670 --> 06:10.620
I locked the cabinets.

06:10.620 --> 06:11.750
Impenetrable.

06:11.750 --> 06:13.960
Look at this open pen,

06:13.960 --> 06:16.120
just sitting here
for anyone to grab!

06:16.120 --> 06:18.420
Babies don't have control
of their arms!

06:18.420 --> 06:20.500
They just wave them all around,
like...

06:20.500 --> 06:21.170
[ Giggles ]

06:22.210 --> 06:23.830
[ Pen clatters ]

06:23.830 --> 06:25.500
See?

06:25.500 --> 06:27.710
That could've easily
been the baby.

06:27.710 --> 06:29.540
We can do better.

06:29.540 --> 06:30.540
I can do better!

06:30.540 --> 06:32.710
Then show me.

06:32.710 --> 06:34.250
In my good eye.

06:34.250 --> 06:36.830
I listened to my co-workers

06:36.830 --> 06:39.120
and read a bunch
of women's magazines.

06:39.120 --> 06:42.000
Some of them talked about
postpartum depression.

06:42.000 --> 06:44.750
It sounds like it might be
what was going on with Bow.

06:44.750 --> 06:46.750
And they also said
a lot of women

06:46.750 --> 06:49.500
don't realize they have it,
so I had to be gentle.

06:49.500 --> 06:52.000
There's my blushing bride.

06:52.000 --> 06:53.330
Dre, that's very sweet,

06:53.330 --> 06:54.710
but could you please stop
looking at me?

06:54.710 --> 06:56.330
You okay, babe?
Yeah, I'm --

06:56.330 --> 06:59.170
I don't know why my eyes
won't stop watering.

06:59.170 --> 07:00.330
I'm sorry.

07:00.330 --> 07:02.080
You know
what might be fun?

07:02.080 --> 07:03.380
What?

07:03.380 --> 07:05.460
If we take this
postpartum-depression quiz

07:05.460 --> 07:07.330
together.

07:07.330 --> 07:09.040
[ Sighs ]
Dre, I don't want to do that.

07:09.040 --> 07:10.750
I'm -- I'm okay.

07:10.750 --> 07:13.960
Totally. Totally.

07:13.960 --> 07:15.420
But I think we should --

07:15.420 --> 07:17.210
we should take it
just in case one of us

07:17.210 --> 07:21.040
has a debilitating
mood disorder, okay?

07:21.040 --> 07:22.580
So, I'll go first.

07:22.580 --> 07:26.830
"Do you feel sad, hopeless,
overwhelmed, empty?"

07:26.830 --> 07:29.080
That's a "nope" for me.

07:29.080 --> 07:30.830
How about you?

07:30.830 --> 07:32.880
Uh...well, I don't know.

07:32.880 --> 07:34.000
I feel sad.

07:34.000 --> 07:35.540
Mm-hmm.

07:35.540 --> 07:36.670
[ Voice breaking ]
And I feel hopeless,

07:36.670 --> 07:37.880
and I feel overwhelmed,

07:37.880 --> 07:39.170
but I don't feel empty,

07:39.170 --> 07:40.500
so I guess it's a "no"
for me.

07:40.500 --> 07:42.960
Okay. This is fun.

07:42.960 --> 07:45.500
Yep.
All right, number two.

07:45.500 --> 07:48.080
"Are you crying
more often than usual?"

07:48.080 --> 07:51.670
I'm just gonna put a "yes"
for you.

07:51.670 --> 07:54.170
Dre, I'm fine. Okay?

07:54.170 --> 07:55.960
It's just,
the baby came early,

07:55.960 --> 07:57.830
and he's not sleeping,
and he's not eating.

07:57.830 --> 07:59.750
I just --
I think he might be cursed.

07:59.750 --> 08:02.250
Ah, that takes us down
to question 17.

08:02.250 --> 08:05.210
"Do you think your baby
is cursed?"

08:05.210 --> 08:07.540
"Yes" for you.

08:07.540 --> 08:09.290
♪♪

08:09.290 --> 08:10.000
Hmm.

08:10.000 --> 08:12.420
...49, 50.

08:12.420 --> 08:14.210
Wow!

08:14.210 --> 08:16.290
49 out of 50.

08:16.290 --> 08:19.540
[ Chuckles ] Babe,
you still acing quizzes.

08:19.540 --> 08:23.580
Yep. According to this,
you just might have postpartum.

08:23.580 --> 08:25.210
Dre, I don't have
postpartum.

08:25.210 --> 08:26.880
I am a doctor,
and I would know.

08:26.880 --> 08:29.080
Totally. Totally.

08:29.080 --> 08:31.830
But maybe we should talk
to another doctor

08:31.830 --> 08:34.040
to confirm that
you don't have it.

08:34.040 --> 08:36.670
Fine.

08:36.670 --> 08:38.170
If that's gonna make you
feel better, fine.

08:38.170 --> 08:39.330
Babe.

08:39.330 --> 08:40.500
Maybe you just need
some help.

08:40.500 --> 08:41.790
All right.

08:41.790 --> 08:43.000
And that's what
we're gonna get you.

08:43.000 --> 08:44.330
I --

08:44.330 --> 08:47.250
Hey, and you don't
have to worry.

08:47.250 --> 08:48.750
I'm not gonna leave you.

08:48.750 --> 08:52.000
[ Stammers ]

08:52.000 --> 08:53.670
Well, I hadn't
thought of that.

08:53.670 --> 08:54.790
[ Scoffs ]

08:54.790 --> 08:56.920
Me...neither. Ha!

09:01.670 --> 09:02.880
Okay, so, the anxiety
and the insomnia and the crying

09:02.880 --> 09:05.250
and the,
uh...constant insecurity,

09:05.250 --> 09:07.120
that's all postpartum?

09:07.120 --> 09:08.500
Most likely.

09:08.500 --> 09:11.420
I mean, that's exactly
what the quiz said.

09:11.420 --> 09:13.880
You want a copy of this
for your files?

09:13.880 --> 09:16.080
We actually have our own

09:16.080 --> 09:18.420
clinically tested and approved
diagnostic protocols,

09:18.420 --> 09:19.960
but thank you.

09:19.960 --> 09:21.880
Huh. Okay.

09:21.880 --> 09:25.250
Um, postpartum manifests itself
differently in every mother.

09:25.250 --> 09:27.620
Some women even have trouble
bonding with their baby.

09:27.620 --> 09:29.580
Really? So --
So bonding is a part of it?

09:29.580 --> 09:30.920
Mm-hmm.

09:30.920 --> 09:33.420
'Cause I've been --

09:33.420 --> 09:35.500
been feeling really guilty

09:35.500 --> 09:37.880
'cause I can't seem to connect
with DeVonté.

09:37.880 --> 09:39.880
That is very normal.

09:39.880 --> 09:41.750
But it didn't happen
with any of my other kids.

09:41.750 --> 09:44.710
W-W-Well, w-with Junior,
it happened with me.

09:44.710 --> 09:47.290
Well, every pregnancy
is different.

09:47.290 --> 09:49.120
And every treatment is,
too.

09:49.120 --> 09:51.000
The sooner we figure out
the right medication for you,

09:51.000 --> 09:53.250
the sooner you will start
feeling like yourself again.

09:53.250 --> 09:55.170
[ Sighs ] No, you know what?
I-I can get through this.

09:55.170 --> 09:57.120
I d--
I don't want medication.

09:57.120 --> 09:59.250
Obviously,
the decision is yours,

09:59.250 --> 10:01.620
but postpartum depression
is a mood disorder.

10:01.620 --> 10:03.380
It's not something
you can just power through,

10:03.380 --> 10:05.420
and it is nothing
to feel ashamed of.

10:05.420 --> 10:07.290
Can I still breastfeed?

10:07.290 --> 10:09.040
'Cause that's really important
to me.

10:09.040 --> 10:12.460
Plus, breastfeeding helps her
lose the baby weight,

10:12.460 --> 10:15.960
and we want to make sure
we keep that going.

10:15.960 --> 10:19.250
What?
I'm your advocate.

10:19.250 --> 10:20.290
My God.

10:20.290 --> 10:22.710
Nursing's completely safe

10:22.710 --> 10:24.170
on the one I'm thinking of.

10:24.170 --> 10:27.170
It takes time to find
the right dosage of medication,

10:27.170 --> 10:28.380
but this is a good
first step.

10:28.380 --> 10:30.710
Uh...

10:30.710 --> 10:33.710
So, does this mean
that she'll stop crying

10:33.710 --> 10:35.420
every time she sees me?

10:35.420 --> 10:37.380
I'm not entirely convinced
that's the postpartum.

10:37.380 --> 10:39.040
♪♪

10:39.040 --> 10:40.540
Hey.

10:40.540 --> 10:41.750
Hey.

10:41.750 --> 10:43.330
How are the "thank you" notes
going?

10:43.330 --> 10:44.830
Good.

10:44.830 --> 10:46.330
Here.

10:46.330 --> 10:48.040
"Thank you for
the dumb wood thing

10:48.040 --> 10:49.620
that has already been
thrown away.

10:49.620 --> 10:51.420
Regards,
Rainbow Johnson."

10:51.420 --> 10:53.830
[ Sighs ] Okay.
Are they all that harsh?

10:53.830 --> 10:55.420
No.

10:55.420 --> 10:57.710
Here.
[ Sighs ]

10:57.710 --> 11:00.290
"Babies hate pewter spoons.
Kill yourself."

11:00.290 --> 11:02.170
That was my gift!

11:02.170 --> 11:04.460
Oh, then you saved me
a stamp.

11:04.460 --> 11:07.460
♪♪

11:07.460 --> 11:10.080
Hey, babe.
You look great.

11:10.080 --> 11:11.750
How you feeling?

11:11.750 --> 11:14.540
It's been two days,
okay?

11:14.540 --> 11:16.710
So I know you mean well,
but you have to stop asking.

11:16.710 --> 11:19.420
Cool, cool.
I totally understand.

11:19.420 --> 11:21.080
Okay.
Hey, how about
we take a run together?

11:21.080 --> 11:22.210
You know,
because the doctor said

11:22.210 --> 11:23.710
it might make you feel
better if...

11:23.710 --> 11:26.080
[ DeVonté cries ]
Please stop trying
to fix me.

11:26.080 --> 11:27.460
Okay.

11:27.460 --> 11:29.420
Okay, I'm -- I'm gonna
go get the baby.

11:29.420 --> 11:31.790
[ Crying continues ]

11:31.790 --> 11:34.830
Are you sure you want to leave
her alone with that child?

11:34.830 --> 11:37.210
They left me alone with you
for years.

11:37.210 --> 11:39.330
Yeah, well, I didn't go
to some quack doctor

11:39.330 --> 11:42.920
because I was mentally ill
with some made-up disease.

11:42.920 --> 11:47.250
It's a real thing
that lots of women get.

11:47.250 --> 11:49.830
And Bow is taking medicine
to get better.

11:49.830 --> 11:51.080
Wait a minute.

11:51.080 --> 11:53.750
She's doing drugs
and nursing my grandson?

11:53.750 --> 11:54.880
Oh.
She's not doing drugs.

11:54.880 --> 11:57.540
Dre, a lady at church
nursed on drugs,

11:57.540 --> 12:00.670
and her son can only make
friends with loose dogs.

12:00.670 --> 12:02.080
Her milk was poison.

12:02.080 --> 12:04.210
So you're a doctor now?

12:04.210 --> 12:05.710
Because you were
smoking a cigarette

12:05.710 --> 12:07.170
while I was being born.

12:07.170 --> 12:09.040
[ Scoffs ]
So was the doctor!

12:09.040 --> 12:11.080
♪♪

12:11.080 --> 12:12.290
We finished
babyproofing!

12:12.290 --> 12:14.000
Yeah, the house
couldn't be safer.

12:14.000 --> 12:16.040
DeVonté isn't gonna get
into anything.

12:16.040 --> 12:17.750
♪♪

12:17.750 --> 12:18.670
[ Door bangs ]

12:18.670 --> 12:23.830
♪♪

12:23.830 --> 12:25.380
Ohh!

12:25.380 --> 12:30.580
♪♪

12:30.580 --> 12:31.920
[ Grunts ]

12:31.920 --> 12:34.500
Wow. Well, I'm glad
you guys handled everything.

12:34.500 --> 12:37.170
I mean, I didn't even think
to do any of that, so...

12:37.170 --> 12:39.250
Why didn't I think of that?

12:39.250 --> 12:42.210
I am the mom.

12:42.210 --> 12:44.040
Why isn't she getting
any better?

12:44.040 --> 12:46.120
She will.
She's gonna be okay.

12:46.120 --> 12:47.120
Are you sure?

12:47.120 --> 12:49.120
She put sunscreen
and a steak knife

12:49.120 --> 12:50.620
in Diane's
lunchbox today.

12:50.620 --> 12:52.460
Turns out I needed both
at recess.

12:52.460 --> 12:56.330
I swear to God
and sweet black Jesus,

12:56.330 --> 12:58.710
y'all put a lock on one more
damn thing in this house,

12:58.710 --> 13:01.750
and I will whip all four
of your asses at the same time!

13:01.750 --> 13:05.330
♪♪

13:05.330 --> 13:06.830
[ Sighs ]

13:06.830 --> 13:09.710
Oh, he's sleeping.

13:09.710 --> 13:11.750
How'd you do that?

13:11.750 --> 13:13.750
I gave him a little something
to eat,

13:13.750 --> 13:15.170
knocked him right out.

13:15.170 --> 13:16.420
[ Stammers ]

13:16.420 --> 13:19.420
Wait.

13:19.420 --> 13:21.250
Why -- Why is all of this
still here?

13:21.250 --> 13:22.540
Yeah, I gave him
some formula.

13:22.540 --> 13:24.960
What?

13:24.960 --> 13:27.120
Ruby...

13:27.120 --> 13:28.540
he's never had formula.

13:28.540 --> 13:30.080
I-I'm just breastfeeding.

13:30.080 --> 13:32.750
Well, I thought your milk
might be keeping him awake,

13:32.750 --> 13:34.250
on account
of the medication.
Oh, my God.

13:34.250 --> 13:36.290
And from the looks of it,
I was right.

13:36.290 --> 13:39.120
Are you kidding me?

13:39.120 --> 13:40.420
What the [bleep]

13:40.420 --> 13:41.920
Okay, just calm down.

13:41.920 --> 13:45.420
No, I'm not gonna calm down,
Ruby.

13:45.420 --> 13:48.170
You know what?
I put up with so much from you.

13:48.170 --> 13:51.830
You make fun of my hair.
You make fun of my clothing.

13:51.830 --> 13:54.540
You make fun of my cooking.
You make fun of my blackness.

13:54.540 --> 13:55.750
It's more your whiteness.

13:55.750 --> 13:57.040
I'm not joking!

13:57.040 --> 13:58.880
You walk all over me,
and I let you.

13:58.880 --> 14:00.580
In my home!

14:00.580 --> 14:02.380
But you've crossed a line.

14:02.380 --> 14:04.210
Hey, I was just trying
to help.

14:04.210 --> 14:05.330
No, you weren't.

14:05.330 --> 14:07.380
You're never just trying
to do anything, Ruby.

14:07.380 --> 14:09.040
You were trying to make me
feel bad.

14:09.040 --> 14:10.250
Oh, come on.
Hey, hey, hey.
What's going on?

14:10.250 --> 14:12.290
No, stay out of it.
Stay out of it, Dre.

14:12.290 --> 14:13.750
Do you think this is easy
for me, Ruby?

14:13.750 --> 14:16.960
Do you?

14:16.960 --> 14:20.380
Motherhood is the most
natural thing for a woman.

14:20.380 --> 14:21.920
And I've had four kids,

14:21.920 --> 14:25.170
and somehow,
I am struggling right now.

14:25.170 --> 14:28.170
I cannot seem to make
enough milk.

14:28.170 --> 14:31.540
I feel filled with anxiety.
I feel weak.

14:31.540 --> 14:34.330
I feel embarrassed because of
all the things that I can't do.

14:34.330 --> 14:36.790
And you are making me feel
so much worse!

14:36.790 --> 14:40.380
Okay, now,
it was just a little formula.

14:40.380 --> 14:43.250
Oh, my God.
Don't you think
maybe you're overreacting?

14:43.250 --> 14:45.330
[ Voice breaking ] I'm not.
I'm just not.

14:45.330 --> 14:46.580
I'm not.

14:46.580 --> 14:48.250
And you need to get
out of my home,

14:48.250 --> 14:50.920
because there's no way I'm gonna
get better while you're here.

14:50.920 --> 14:53.460
So you need to leave, and you
cannot live here anymore.

14:53.460 --> 14:54.380
You need to go.

14:54.380 --> 14:56.580
Andre,
she's acting crazy.

14:56.580 --> 14:57.920
And you need to talk to her,
okay?

14:57.920 --> 15:00.000
No, Mama.

15:00.000 --> 15:02.580
Not this time.

15:02.580 --> 15:04.210
You got to go.

15:04.210 --> 15:13.540
♪♪

15:13.540 --> 15:15.920
[ Cries ]
It's okay, baby.

15:20.710 --> 15:22.250
It had been a little while
since we saw the doctor

15:22.250 --> 15:23.620
and things in the house
were still messed up.

15:23.620 --> 15:25.580
My mother was gone.

15:25.580 --> 15:28.710
My kids were freaked out
about their mom...

15:28.710 --> 15:30.790
Everything's gonna be
all right.

15:30.790 --> 15:34.880
...because Bow
still wasn't herself.

15:34.880 --> 15:38.000
I felt like I was the only one
holding it together.

15:40.380 --> 15:43.460
Can't handle a baby gate, son?
[ Chuckles ]

15:46.080 --> 15:47.460
What happened
to your hand?

15:47.460 --> 15:50.500
Aah!

15:50.500 --> 15:51.960
Damn!

15:51.960 --> 15:53.210
I was gonna sweep it up,

15:53.210 --> 15:54.540
but I couldn't get
into the pantry.

15:56.540 --> 15:58.210
You're looking at me like
you want to say something.

15:58.210 --> 16:00.330
You might as well go ahead
and spit it out.

16:00.330 --> 16:03.540
Look, I would usually talk
to Bow about this,

16:03.540 --> 16:05.250
or Moms, but I can't.

16:05.250 --> 16:07.540
I have nobody else
to talk to, obviously,

16:07.540 --> 16:10.250
which is why
I'm talking to you.

16:10.250 --> 16:12.080
Oh,
and I'm a bad choice.

16:13.960 --> 16:15.580
I'm just worried, Pops.

16:15.580 --> 16:16.420
We really doing this?

16:20.040 --> 16:21.580
Pour me another drink.

16:21.580 --> 16:23.290
All right.

16:23.290 --> 16:25.170
I feel like
I'm in this alone.

16:25.170 --> 16:27.420
You know,
the kids are scared.

16:27.420 --> 16:29.120
I'm trying my best
to comfort them,

16:29.120 --> 16:31.920
but I'm just as scared
as they are.

16:31.920 --> 16:34.750
I barely recognize my wife.

16:36.040 --> 16:38.460
What if she's never
herself again?

16:38.460 --> 16:40.000
Well, why are you
borrowing trouble?

16:40.000 --> 16:41.750
All you can do
is support her now

16:41.750 --> 16:44.040
and give her a little time
to get back on track.

16:44.040 --> 16:47.750
Everybody says that --
"Give it time."

16:47.750 --> 16:51.330
I want to do something.
I feel so powerless.

16:51.330 --> 16:53.290
You've been doing everything
you can do.

16:53.290 --> 16:55.250
I've been watching you.

16:55.250 --> 16:56.620
You've been
holding it down.

16:59.040 --> 17:02.080
That's...dangerously close
to praise, Pops.

17:02.080 --> 17:04.210
Well,
I lost a lot of blood.

17:07.750 --> 17:09.830
[ DeVonté cooing ]

17:09.830 --> 17:12.670
[ Whispering ] Why is there so
much broken glass in this house?

17:12.670 --> 17:15.540
♪♪

17:19.290 --> 17:21.330
[ Sighs ]

17:21.330 --> 17:23.040
Ruby, what are you
doing here?

17:23.040 --> 17:25.960
I hope it's okay
I used my key to get in.

17:25.960 --> 17:29.000
Look, I just felt like
I really needed to talk to you.

17:29.000 --> 17:32.210
Okay.

17:32.210 --> 17:33.920
I've been doing a lot
of thinking,

17:33.920 --> 17:35.790
and I realize
you were right.

17:35.790 --> 17:38.000
I overstepped
with the formula.

17:38.000 --> 17:39.620
What are you saying?

17:39.620 --> 17:42.330
[ Sighs ]

17:42.330 --> 17:44.120
I crossed the line.

17:44.120 --> 17:46.330
I would've thrown me out,
too.

17:49.670 --> 17:51.750
You listen to me,
Rainbow.

17:51.750 --> 17:54.960
You've got nothing
to be ashamed of.

17:54.960 --> 17:57.290
You're a good mother.
Unh...

17:57.290 --> 17:58.790
I do not feel like
a good mother.

17:58.790 --> 18:00.330
Well, you are.

18:00.330 --> 18:03.380
And you're not weak,
because you got help.

18:03.380 --> 18:05.750
I'm weak for not being there
to help you get it.

18:07.920 --> 18:09.670
So I'm sorry.

18:11.790 --> 18:13.420
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm sorry.

18:13.420 --> 18:15.620
I don't think
you've ever said that before.

18:15.620 --> 18:17.920
Me, neither.

18:17.920 --> 18:21.750
Wow. Well...
thank you, Ruby.

18:21.750 --> 18:23.540
That means a lot to me.
It really does.

18:23.540 --> 18:25.670
I hope I can
earn your trust again.

18:25.670 --> 18:27.420
Oh, Ruby.

18:27.420 --> 18:28.880
I never trusted you.

18:28.880 --> 18:31.120
[ Chuckles ]
Smart lady.

18:31.120 --> 18:33.080
[ Chuckles ]
Can I have my key back?

18:33.080 --> 18:34.710
♪♪

18:34.710 --> 18:36.460
Hey, babe.

18:36.460 --> 18:38.710
How are --
You know what?

18:38.710 --> 18:40.290
I'm not even gonna
ask you that.

18:40.290 --> 18:43.710
Nor pry into
your personal writings.

18:43.710 --> 18:46.330
As a matter of fact, I don't
even know why I came out here.

18:46.330 --> 18:49.290
My therapist is making me write
in this journal.

18:49.290 --> 18:51.500
It's actually helping.

18:51.500 --> 18:53.920
Especially after the first
10 pages of writing,

18:53.920 --> 18:55.710
"My therapist is stupid

18:55.710 --> 18:57.620
for having me
write in this journal."

18:57.620 --> 18:59.290
[ Laughs ]

18:59.290 --> 19:00.500
Well,
I'm glad it's helping.

19:00.500 --> 19:01.750
Yeah.

19:01.750 --> 19:03.540
It's nice to see you
smile again.

19:03.540 --> 19:05.830
Babe.

19:05.830 --> 19:07.670
Hmm?

19:07.670 --> 19:09.250
[ Sighs ]

19:09.250 --> 19:11.080
I really appreciate
how you've been there for me,

19:11.080 --> 19:12.330
especially with your mom.

19:12.330 --> 19:13.750
Of course.

19:13.750 --> 19:17.080
You think I'd ever take her side
over yours?

19:17.080 --> 19:19.000
That's exactly
what I think.

19:19.000 --> 19:20.670
You're my wife --

19:20.670 --> 19:25.000
the most important person
in my life.

19:25.000 --> 19:26.460
But you're gonna let my mama
move back in, right?

19:26.460 --> 19:27.790
Eventually.

19:27.790 --> 19:29.380
I'm not gonna let her stay
in that hotel forever.

19:29.380 --> 19:31.580
Yeah, well, they're not gonna
let her stay long, either.

19:31.580 --> 19:33.080
She's already been banned
from the hotel pool

19:33.080 --> 19:34.500
for sunbathing topless.

19:34.500 --> 19:35.710
What? Ugh.

19:35.710 --> 19:37.080
The restaurant, too.

19:37.080 --> 19:38.670
Same reason.

19:38.670 --> 19:39.880
Wow. Okay.

19:39.880 --> 19:41.330
♪♪

19:41.330 --> 19:43.620
Rainbow: Where's DeVonté?
Where's DeVonté?

19:43.620 --> 19:45.620
[ Gasps ]
Where's DeVonté?

19:45.620 --> 19:48.210
Oh, God!
Mom lost the baby.

19:48.210 --> 19:50.580
Don't worry.
We'll find him.

19:50.580 --> 19:52.460
There he is.

19:52.460 --> 19:54.000
Oh, hey, guys.

19:54.000 --> 19:55.330
Hey, Mom, do you want me
to take him?

19:55.330 --> 19:57.080
No, that's okay.
Keep your shirt on.

19:57.080 --> 19:59.040
Thank God.
He keeps trying to latch.

20:00.540 --> 20:04.120
So [sighs] guys,
I really appreciate

20:04.120 --> 20:05.420
everything that
you've done.

20:05.420 --> 20:07.460
I know it's been really hard
around here

20:07.460 --> 20:09.710
and maybe
a little scary, too.

20:09.710 --> 20:15.210
But this is just something
that sometimes happens to moms.

20:15.210 --> 20:17.080
It's a part of life.

20:17.080 --> 20:21.500
It's a really crappy
part of life.

20:21.500 --> 20:23.120
And I'm gonna be okay.

20:23.120 --> 20:24.670
I promise.

20:24.670 --> 20:27.040
And, Diane...

20:27.040 --> 20:28.170
maybe we should take
a little break

20:28.170 --> 20:29.290
from the
"thank you" notes.

20:29.290 --> 20:31.000
You've burned
a lot of bridges.

20:31.000 --> 20:32.750
You're welcome.

20:32.750 --> 20:34.330
Oh, okay.

20:34.330 --> 20:36.120
Dre: Oh, hey, guys.
There you are.

20:36.120 --> 20:38.040
Hey.

20:38.040 --> 20:41.790
So I didn't have to ask Bow
how she was feeling anymore.

20:41.790 --> 20:45.290
I could see she was on her way.

20:50.330 --> 20:51.920
Diane:
"Dear Josh, thank you for the
baby blanket you made by hand.

20:51.920 --> 20:53.580
We will hold it up to DeVonté

20:53.580 --> 20:56.040
to show him that sometimes
trying isn't enough.

20:56.040 --> 20:59.000
Best, Rainbow Johnson."

20:59.000 --> 21:03.460
"Dear Mr. Stevens, thank you
for the soul food delivery.

21:03.460 --> 21:06.250
You really know black people."

21:06.250 --> 21:08.580
I really do.

21:08.580 --> 21:10.210
♪♪

21:10.210 --> 21:14.120
"Hello, Charles.
I now have your home address.

21:14.120 --> 21:16.790
It's the last mistake
you'll make.

21:16.790 --> 21:19.710
Soon, Diane Johnson."

21:19.710 --> 21:23.500
♪♪
